  "text": "In the Apache Kafka codebase (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489), audit logging for authorization decisions is primarily handled by the StandardAuthorizerData class located at metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/StandardAuthorizerData.java. This class implements audit trail functionality for ACL decisions through its logAuditMessage() method (lines 281-310), which logs both ALLOWED and DENIED authorization events to the 'kafka.authorizer.logger' logger. The method is called from the authorize() method (line 250) in the same class, which evaluates authorization decisions and determines whether access is ALLOWED or DENIED. The StandardAuthorizer class (metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/StandardAuthorizer.java) serves as the main built-in authorizer implementation that uses StandardAuthorizerData to perform authorization checks. The audit logging distinguishes between ALLOWED events that are logged at DEBUG level when logIfAllowed is true (lines 292-296), and DENIED events that are logged at INFO level when logIfDenied is true (lines 304-308). This design allows fine-grained control over audit logging through the logIfAllowed and logIfDenied flags in the Action class, enabling auditors to track explicit authorization failures while filtering out informational queries."
}

